Russia RTS Stock-Index Futures Gain 0.2% at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-05-03T15:10:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/russia-rts-stock-index-futures-gain-0-2-at-start-of-trading.html
Russia ’s RTS futures expiring in June
added 0.2 percent to 194,035 at 11:02 a.m. in  New York .  OAO Gazprom, the natural-gas export monopoly, rose 0.4
percent. Contracts on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-biggest
oil producer, advanced 0.1 percent, while contracts on OAO
Sberbank, Russia’s largest lender, gained 0.2 percent.  The Market Vectors Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that
holds Russian shares, dropped 2.7 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
 hpavliva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
